error.signature: TS2345: Argument of type 'X' is not assignable to parameter of type 'Y'
error.regex: TS2345: Argument of type ['\"]?(.+?)['\"]? is not assignable to parameter

verdict.summary: Function argument doesn't match the expected parameter type.

dead_ends.why_fails: Type assertion can hide real bugs if the runtime value doesn't match

dead_ends.action: Change the function parameter to accept any
dead_ends.why_fails: Removes type safety for all callers

workarounds.action: Transform the argument to match the expected type before passing
Use function overloads or generics to accept multiple types safely

leads_to.condition: Fixing argument types leads to discovering untyped parameters

preceded_by.condition: Fixing assignment types reveals argument mismatches in function calls

frequently_confused_with.distinction: TS2322 is about assignment to variables/properties; TS2345 is specifically about function call arguments
